  "title": "Ordering Food at a Restaurant in Darija",
  "dialect": "darija",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Greeting the Waiter/Waitress",
          "arabic": "تحية النادل/النّادلة"
        },
        "text": "When you enter a restaurant, you'll first need to greet the staff. In Darija, a common polite greeting is 'Salam 3alikom' (Peace be upon you). You can then use '3afak' (please) when asking for something.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "سلام عليكم.",
            "english": "Hello / Peace be upon you.",
            "transliteration": "Salam 3alikom."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عافاك.",
            "english": "Please.",
            "transliteration": "3afak."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "سلام عليكم. عافاك."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking for a Table",
          "arabic": "طلب طاولة"
        },
        "text": "After greeting, you'll likely need to ask for a table. The word for table is 'tabla'. To ask for one, you can say 'Bghit tabla 3afak' (I want a table, please) or 'Kayna chi tabla khawya?' (Is there an empty table?).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بغيت طبلة عافاك.",
            "english": "I want a table, please.",
            "transliteration": "Bghit tabla 3afak."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "كايْنَة شي طبلة خاوْيَة؟",
            "english": "Is there an empty table?",
            "transliteration": "Kayna chi tabla khawya?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "بغيت طبلة عافاك. كاينة شي طبلة خاوية؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Calling the Waiter",
          "arabic": "النداء على النادل"
        },
        "text": "If you need to get the waiter's attention, you can use 'Serveur!' (Waiter!) or 'Khoya!' (My brother!, for a male waiter) or 'Khti!' (My sister!, for a female waitress). These are common and polite ways to call someone over.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "سيرفور!",
            "english": "Waiter!",
            "transliteration": "Serveur!"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "خويا عافاك.",
            "english": "Brother, please (excuse me/waiter).",
            "transliteration": "Khoya 3afak."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "سيرفور! خويا عافاك."
      }
    },
