    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking for the Menu",
          "arabic": "طلب قائمة الطعام"
        },
        "text": "Once seated, you'll need the menu to choose your food. In Darija, 'menu' is commonly referred to as 'Ménu' (borrowed from French) or sometimes 'Carte'. You can say '3afak l-ménu' (Please, the menu).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "عافاك الموني.",
            "english": "Please, the menu.",
            "transliteration": "3afak l-ménu."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش ممكن تعطيني الموني؟",
            "english": "Can you give me the menu?",
            "transliteration": "Wash momkin ta3tini l-ménu?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "عافاك الموني. واش ممكن تعطيني الموني؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking for Recommendations",
          "arabic": "طلب اقتراحات"
        },
        "text": "If you're unsure what to order, you can ask the waiter for recommendations. You can say 'Ach kayn bnīn?' (What's delicious?) or 'Ach katnṣeḥni?' (What do you recommend? - to a male) / 'Ach katnṣeḥīnī?' (What do you recommend? - to a female).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أش كاين بنين؟",
            "english": "What's delicious?",
            "transliteration": "Ach kayn bnīn?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أش كَتْنْصَحْنِي؟",
            "english": "What do you recommend? (to male)",
            "transliteration": "Ach katnṣeḥni?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أش كَتْنْصَحِينِي؟",
            "english": "What do you recommend? (to female)",
            "transliteration": "Ach katnṣeḥini?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "أش كاين بنين؟ أش كتنصحني؟ أش كتنصحيني؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing Preferences / Dietary Needs",
          "arabic": "التعبير عن التفضيلات/الاحتياجات الغذائية"
        },
        "text": "It's useful to know how to express if you don't eat certain things. 'Ma kanākoulch...' (I don't eat...) or 'Ma kanbghich...' (I don't like...). For example, 'Ma kanākoulch l-ḥam' (I don't eat meat).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ما كناكلش الحوت.",
            "english": "I don't eat fish.",
            "transliteration": "Ma kanākoulch l-ḥout."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "ما كنبغيش الحار.",
            "english": "I don't like spicy food.",
            "transliteration": "Ma kanbghich l-ḥār."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "ما كناكلش الحوت. ما كنبغيش الحار."
      }
    },
