    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Ordering Drinks",
          "arabic": "طلب المشروبات"
        },
        "text": "Drinks are an essential part of any meal. 'Ma' (water) is commonly ordered. You can ask for 'Ma dial ṣ-ṣḥḥa' (Bottled water) or 'Atay' (Tea). 'Café' (Coffee) is also common. Remember to use '3afak' (please).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بغيت ما ديال الصحة عافاك.",
            "english": "I want bottled water, please.",
            "transliteration": "Bghit ma dial ṣ-ṣḥḥa 3afak."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "جوج أتاي، عافاك.",
            "english": "Two teas, please.",
            "transliteration": "Jūj atay, 3afak."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "بغيت ما ديال الصحة عافاك. جوج أتاي، عافاك."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Ordering Side Dishes",
          "arabic": "طلب الأطباق الجانبية"
        },
        "text": "You might want to order side dishes like salads or fries. 'Chlada' (salad) and 'Batata mqlīya' (fries) are common. You can use the 'Bghit...' (I want...) structure again.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بغيت شلاضة مغربية.",
            "english": "I want a Moroccan salad.",
            "transliteration": "Bghit chlada maghribiya."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش عندكم بطاطا مقلية؟",
